# Archium Agent Skills

When the task involves architectural presentation authoring, drawing/photo layout, renovation report narrative, Studio element comments, or visual QA, **Read** the matching skill file under `archium-agent-skills/` before acting. Do not invent parallel rules.

## Skill map

| Trigger | Skill path |
|---------|------------|
| Building decks, narrative, facts, slide rules | `archium-agent-skills/architectural-presentation-authoring/SKILL.md` |
| Site plan / floor plan / section pages | `archium-agent-skills/drawing-page-design/SKILL.md` |
| Photo evidence boards, site issues | `archium-agent-skills/photo-evidence-layout/SKILL.md` |
| Executive summary, cover thesis, closing | `archium-agent-skills/executive-summary-writing/SKILL.md` |
| Hospital / medical renovation reports | `archium-agent-skills/hospital-renovation-report/SKILL.md` |
| Campus renovation reports | `archium-agent-skills/campus-renovation-report/SKILL.md` |
| Element comments, NL edit on selected node, proposals | `archium-agent-skills/apply-studio-comments/SKILL.md` |
| Visual QA, north arrow, crop, overflow review | `archium-agent-skills/visual-qa-review/SKILL.md` |

## Rules

1. Prefer the skill checklist over ad-hoc style advice.
2. Stack skills when needed (domain + authoring + QA).
3. Keep `archium-agent-skills/` as the single source of truth; do not duplicate long rules into this file.
